  "text": "Coloring random graphs with hereditary properties: In [CITATION_1] , Bollobás and Thomason estimated the coloring number of random graphs by graphs satisfying some hereditary property. As they noticed, finding the probability that a random graph G(n, p) satisfies some hereditary property is much more difficult when p = 1 2 . Their approach is also based on the regularity lemma together with tools from the theory of Random Graphs, and is strongly related to some of our methods here.",
